!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

vault /vɔːlt/

(vaulting,vaulted,vaults) 

1. N-COUNT A vault is a secure room where money and other valuable things can be kept safely. 保险库 

例： Most of the money was in storage in bank vaults. 这笔钱的一大部分是存放在银行保险库中的。 

2. N-COUNT A vault is a room underneath a church or in a cemetery where people are buried, usually the members of a single family. 家族墓穴 

例： He ordered that Matilda's body should be buried in the family vault. 他下命令说玛蒂尔达的尸体要埋葬在家族墓穴中。 

3. N an arched structure that forms a roof or ceiling 拱顶; 穹隆 

4. V-T/V-I If you vault something or vault over it, you jump quickly onto or over it, especially by putting a hand on top of it to help you balance while you jump. (尤指以手支撑的) 跃过; 跳跃 

例： He could easily vault the wall. 他可以轻而易举地跃过这堵墙。 

5. N the act of vaulting 跳跃 

6. V to furnish with or as if with an arched roof 以穹隆来装饰

